    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Automate a multi-step process with HTTP / REST API and MySQL in real time\n\n**Pattern:** Workflow Automation · **Level:** Foundation · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nAutomate a multi-step process with HTTP / REST API and MySQL in real time. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual summarization is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nHourly Schedule → Route by Work Type → Process 'sync' → MySQL → Merge Routed Work → Align Field Names\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to workflow automation without manual effort\n- Anyone automating summarization in ai\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Scales without extra headcount\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: MySQL connection; Telegram bot token.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "dbaf4275-c302-99ec-3f94-1a04c0c98960",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your summarization process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
